  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(GUK) Integrated Emergency Humanitarian Response to the Rohingya Population in Cox&#x2019;s Bazar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">All details below outline consortium details, not just this partner.

In line with the Humanitarian Response Plan Strategic Objectives, the response will follow  a coordinated, integrated and inclusive intervention to fill critical gaps in existing humanitarian assistance in WASH, Health, Nutrition and Protection and Health on camp no 12,13,14,15,18 and 19. 

This is a consortium project led by CA, with VW, Concern Worldwide, GUK and DAM.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safe, clean, inclusive and dignified water and sanitation facilities provided.
Comprehensive and inclusive primary health provision and surveillance for FDMN provided.
Provision of malnutrition prevention interventions to improve the nutritional status of affected population (girls, boys, adolescent girls and PLWs).
Protection support system strengthened, and social cohesion promoted with FDMN and host communities.</narrative>
  </description>
